# Project Directory Structure

This rule lists the main source folders and important files so new code
is added in the right place.

## Root

- `package.json`: root Node/Express app metadata and scripts
- `public`: static assets served by the backend (if used)
- `src`: backend Node/Express source code
- `frontend`: React SPA (client) application

Tooling and build artefacts:

- `node_modules`: installed dependencies (do not edit)
- `.cursor`: Cursor configuration and rules

## Backend (`src`)

- `src/server.js`: Express app entry point, middleware wiring, and routes
- `src/config/db.js`: database connection configuration
- `src/middleware/asyncHandler.js`: async route wrapper
- `src/middleware/authMiddleware.js`: auth-related middleware
- `src/middleware/errorMiddleware.js`: error handler middleware
- `src/utils/generateToken.js`: helper for token generation

When adding new backend features:

- keep route logic in controllers and wire them through routes
- keep DB-specific logic and schemas in models
- put cross-cutting concerns (auth, validation, logging) in middleware
- keep pure helpers in `src/utils`

## Frontend (`frontend`)

- `frontend/package.json`: React app metadata and scripts
- `frontend/public`: static HTML shell, manifest, icons, and public assets
- `frontend/src`: React application source

### Frontend `src`

Top-level files:

- `frontend/src/index.js`: React entry point and app bootstrap
- `frontend/src/App.js`: main app shell and layout
- `frontend/src/Routes.js`: central route configuration
- `frontend/src/store.js`: Redux store configuration
- `frontend/src/constants.js`: shared constants for the client
- `frontend/src/index.css`, `frontend/src/App.css`: global styles
- `frontend/src/logo.svg`: app logo asset
- `frontend/src/reportWebVitals.js`, `frontend/src/setupTests.js`:
  CRA metrics and test setup

Domain-specific folders:

- `frontend/src/assets/styles`:
  shared CSS such as `bootstrap.custom.css`, `index.css`
- `frontend/src/screens`:
  page-level components (e.g. `HomeScreen.jsx`) mapped to routes
- `frontend/src/slices`:
  Redux Toolkit slices (e.g. `apiSlice.js`, `authSlice.js`)
- `frontend/src/components`:
  reusable UI components (currently empty or to be populated)
- `frontend/src/utils`:
  frontend utilities (currently empty or to be populated)

When adding new frontend features:

- create route-driven pages under `screens`
- add Redux state and async logic in `slices`
- build reusable pieces in `components`
- keep styling consistent by using `assets/styles` and global CSS
